  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nThe code of the `ERC721.safeTransferFrom` function is inconsistent with the doc of the interface `IERC721.safeTransferFrom`. \r\nThe `IERC721.safeTransferFrom` interface function explicitly requires that parameter `from` cannot be the zero address.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/848fef5b6c39333a2f9f1fb352cca7c188c3754b/contracts/token/ERC721/IERC721.sol#L67\r\n\r\nHowever, in the implementation function `ERC721.safeTransferFrom`, this particular requirement is not enforced by either itself or its callee functions, while all other requirements of this interface are enforced with `require` statements.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/848fef5b6c39333a2f9f1fb352cca7c188c3754b/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol#L161-L170\r\n\r\nThe `ERC721.transferFrom` and `ERC721._safeTransfer` functions also have the same inconsistency issue.\r\n\r\nA potential fix could be adding a `require(from != address(0), \"ERC721...\")` statement in this part of the `ERC721._transfer` function:\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/848fef5b6c39333a2f9f1fb352cca7c188c3754b/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721.sol#L336-L337\r\n\r\nCould you please check it?\r\n\r\nThanks. ",
